-- models/intermediate/int_deduped_billing_events.sql
-- Deduplicate billing_events to one row per subscription and event_month
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        event_id,
        subscription_id,
        event_month,
        amount,
        event_type,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY subscription_id, event_month
            ORDER BY event_id DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_billing_events') }}
)
SELECT
    event_id,
    subscription_id,
    event_month,
    amount,
    event_type
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

```sql
-- models/mart/fct_monthly_subscription_metrics.sql
-- Calculate monthly subscription metrics grouped by month, tier, and industry
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        DATE_TRUNC('month', b.event_month) AS month,
        COALESCE(p.tier, '(unknown)') AS tier,
        COALESCE(c.industry, '(unknown)') AS industry,
        s.subscription_id,
        p.monthly_price,
        s.user_id
    FROM {{ ref('int_deduped_billing_events') }} b
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_subscriptions') }} s
        ON s.subscription_id = b.subscription_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_users') }} u
        ON u.user_id = s.user_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_companies') }} c
        ON c.company_id = u.company_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_plans') }} p
        ON p.plan_id = s.plan_id
    WHERE s.status = 'active'
)
SELECT
    month,
    tier,
    industry,
    COUNT(DISTINCT subscription_id) AS active_subscriptions,
    SUM(monthly_price) AS total_mrr,
    COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) AS unique_users
FROM source
GROUP BY
    month,
    tier,
    industry
ORDER BY
    month DESC,
    tier,
    industry
